1
00:00:57,849 --> 00:00:59,518
- Hello?
- It's me.

2
00:00:59,601 --> 00:01:02,312
Oh, am I bothering you, Francesco?

3
00:01:02,479 --> 00:01:05,607
No, don't worry, I had to get
out of the shower some time.

4
00:01:05,857 --> 00:01:07,401
Hold on a minute, Franco...

5
00:01:28,213 --> 00:01:29,673
You were saying, Franco?

6
00:01:29,881 --> 00:01:33,260
No, no, nothing. Just
calling to see how you doing.

7
00:01:33,927 --> 00:01:35,429
You know how things are...

8
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:41,685
...life goes on.

9
00:02:14,593 --> 00:02:16,052
Gnaghi!

10
00:02:44,331 --> 00:02:47,459
I've been shouting at
you for hours. Gnaghi!

11
00:03:04,309 --> 00:03:06,394
He's Ghigini, the surveyor.

12
00:03:06,895 --> 00:03:09,272
- 12th row, 3rd grave, right?
- Gna.

13
00:03:22,786 --> 00:03:24,037
Grave three.

14
00:03:25,747 --> 00:03:27,040
Here we go.

15
00:03:27,874 --> 00:03:29,668
I know you've heard this before,

16
00:03:30,001 --> 00:03:31,127
but this time,

17
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:33,213
my dear Ghigini,

18
00:03:33,755 --> 00:03:35,548
it is forever.

19
00:03:36,675 --> 00:03:38,218
Rest in peace!

20
00:03:40,971 --> 00:03:42,514
Oh, my back...

21
00:03:51,898 --> 00:03:53,233
What a waste of good marble.

22
00:03:53,441 --> 00:03:54,776
Never looks right when you fix it.

23
00:03:54,985 --> 00:03:56,861
All this fancy packaging.

24
00:03:56,987 --> 00:03:59,614
I don' know why they don't
just cover the graves with dirt.

25
00:04:49,998 --> 00:04:52,459
The gun! I forgot the fucking gun!

26
00:04:53,126 --> 00:04:55,920
- Ea...t!
- Gnaghi,

27
00:04:56,421 --> 00:04:58,214
give me the spade! Gnaghi!

28
00:04:58,381 --> 00:05:00,008
give me the fucking spade!

29
00:05:12,187 --> 00:05:13,438
There we go.

30
00:05:16,858 --> 00:05:19,194
You handle the rest Gnaghi.

31
00:05:20,111 --> 00:05:23,072
My name is Francesco Dellamorte.

32
00:05:23,323 --> 00:05:24,616
Weird name, isn't it?

33
00:05:24,824 --> 00:05:26,159
Francis Of Death.

34
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:28,661
Saint Francis Of Death.

35
00:05:29,078 --> 00:05:31,039
I often thought of having it changed.

36
00:05:31,247 --> 00:05:34,125
Andrea Dellamorte would
be nicer, for example.

37
00:05:34,542 --> 00:05:37,170
I'm the watchman of
the Buffalora cemetery,

38
00:05:37,670 --> 00:05:39,714
I don't know how the epidemic started,

39
00:05:39,923 --> 00:05:43,343
All I know is that some people,
on the 7th night after their death

40
00:05:43,551 --> 00:05:45,261
come back to life.

41
00:05:45,428 --> 00:05:47,764
I call them "Returners",

42
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:51,601
but frankly I can't understand
why they're so anxious to return.

43
00:05:51,935 --> 00:05:54,187
The only way to get rid
of them once and for all,

44
00:05:54,354 --> 00:05:56,064
is to split their heads open.

45
00:05:56,272 --> 00:05:59,484
A spade'll do it, but a
Dum-Dum bullet is best.

46
00:05:59,818 --> 00:06:01,653
Come and have a glass of wine.

47
00:06:04,739 --> 00:06:08,701
Is this the beginning of an invasion?
Does it happen in all cemeteries,

48
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:11,746
or is Buffalora just an exception?

49
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:15,542
Who knows? And in the end, who cares?

50
00:06:16,543 --> 00:06:18,419
I'm just doing my job.

51
00:06:26,219 --> 00:06:29,556
Good morning engineer.
How are you doing today?

52
00:06:29,597 --> 00:06:31,849
Fine, Miss Chiaromondo. And you?

53
00:06:32,058 --> 00:06:33,851
The cemetery is open, isn't it?

54
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:35,937
For you, any time.

55
00:06:37,814 --> 00:06:40,483
Hello cutie. Here...

56
00:06:41,150 --> 00:06:42,819
How are you?

57
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:46,281
He's happy. He likes
it when the sun shines.

58
00:06:52,412 --> 00:06:54,289
I'm not an engineer...

59
00:06:56,749 --> 00:06:58,835
...and you are no cutie.

60
00:07:06,968 --> 00:07:10,263
Poor Gnaghi, on his ID card it reads:

61
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:13,391
"Distinctive physical marks: all".

62
00:07:15,852 --> 00:07:17,937
He has a real passion for dead leaves,

63
