not to think about life.

66
00:08:42,313 --> 00:08:45,525
The most beautiful living
woman I have ever seen!

67
00:08:48,152 --> 00:08:50,029
Will I see her again?

68
00:09:19,183 --> 00:09:22,478
I just came to water the flowers
on your poor father's grave.

69
00:09:24,939 --> 00:09:26,774
Husband.

70
00:09:31,487 --> 00:09:33,072
How long has he been dead?

71
00:09:35,783 --> 00:09:37,243
Two weeks.

72
00:09:37,243 --> 00:09:39,203
- Thank goodness.
- What?

73
00:09:39,370 --> 00:09:43,082
- I mean, I'm very sorry.
- Have you no respect for pain?

74
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:44,750
Well, you know how these
things are... You see:

75
00:09:45,209 --> 00:09:48,504
- in time, pain heals.
- It's not healing a bit.

76
00:09:53,509 --> 00:09:55,219
He was wonderful,

77
00:09:55,511 --> 00:09:58,723
he was a wonderful lover, incredible,

78
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:00,683
tireless.

79
00:10:02,685 --> 00:10:04,895
He was fantastic!

80
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:35,426
I messed it all up,

81
00:10:35,634 --> 00:10:37,094
I've lost her.

82
00:10:38,137 --> 00:10:40,264
Will I see her again?

83
00:10:50,274 --> 00:10:51,400
Hey, Franco!

84
00:10:56,405 --> 00:10:58,574
Franco is the only living person

85
00:10:58,699 --> 00:11:01,410
who even calls me. Now and
then I stop by his office

86
00:11:01,619 --> 00:11:03,913
to remind myself what he looks like.

87
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:06,290
You can't live on memories alone.

88
00:11:12,671 --> 00:11:14,423
It's for you. Sign as usual.

89
00:11:17,885 --> 00:11:20,846
- Have you got a pen?
- No.

90
00:11:21,013 --> 00:11:22,932
Hold on a sec, here we are.

91
00:11:28,395 --> 00:11:30,064
Have you had any visits last nights?

92
00:11:30,272 --> 00:11:31,732
A couple, yes.

93
00:11:34,443 --> 00:11:37,655
All this extra work! It's
much if the pay me any more.

94
00:11:37,988 --> 00:11:39,490
Tell the Mayor...

95
00:11:39,698 --> 00:11:42,993
Oh, tell the Mayor then what?
They'd close the cemetery.

96
00:11:43,077 --> 00:11:44,954
Good-bye job and
good-bye house!

97
00:11:45,204 --> 00:11:47,373
Come on, who do you
think would believe you?

98
00:11:47,456 --> 00:11:49,416
Listen, I don't care if
you don't believe me Franco,

99
00:11:49,583 --> 00:11:51,293
you're not the one who pays me!

100
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:52,753
I believe you,

101
00:11:52,962 --> 00:11:55,005
I believe you, and you're right...

102
00:11:55,214 --> 00:11:57,007
- At least have him pay the overtime.
- Good.

103
00:11:57,216 --> 00:11:58,592
Well, let's go to the Mayor, then!

104
00:11:58,968 --> 00:12:00,219
It's not that easy.

105
00:12:00,719 --> 00:12:03,139
First you have to fill out an M3 form,

106
00:12:03,305 --> 00:12:06,058
