110
00:12:15,609 --> 00:12:17,820
One M3 form!

111
00:12:18,988 --> 00:12:20,531
Going to get our willies wet tonight?

112
00:12:20,739 --> 00:12:22,491
Some of us, yeah.

113
00:12:24,952 --> 00:12:27,413
Hell, at a certain point
in life, you realize

114
00:12:27,621 --> 00:12:29,915
you know more dead people than living.

115
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:44,365
Sorry about the other day, I was
a bit crass. I didn't mean to be.

116
00:13:44,573 --> 00:13:46,784
My name's Francesco Dellamorte.

117
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:50,454
You know, this is the
only job I could get

118
00:13:50,537 --> 00:13:53,040
even with a degree in biology.

119
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:57,836
Anyway we all end up here
sooner or later, don't we?

120
00:13:58,879 --> 00:14:01,548
I've got a great little
house... Want to see it?

121
00:14:03,217 --> 00:14:05,761
I don't live alone, I've
got a helper, Gnaghi.

122
00:14:05,969 --> 00:14:08,055
He's a real conversationist!

123
00:14:10,641 --> 00:14:13,644
The cemetery's small, but
it's got a marvellous ossuary!

124
00:14:17,523 --> 00:14:19,108
An ossuary...

125
00:14:33,038 --> 00:14:35,791
I have never seen anything so...

126
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:37,751
exciting!

127
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:39,086
Neither have I.

128
00:15:11,869 --> 00:15:13,620
It's like in my dreams!

129
00:15:13,954 --> 00:15:15,789
This is my dream.

130
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:20,127
I couldn't ask for anything more.

131
00:15:20,294 --> 00:15:21,044
Me neither.

132
00:15:26,466 --> 00:15:30,179
You know, you've got
a real nice ossuary.

133
00:15:30,804 --> 00:15:31,972
Thanks.

134
00:15:33,849 --> 00:15:36,476
You will allow me to return, won't you?

135
00:15:37,936 --> 00:15:40,439
You will allow me to kiss
you just once, won't you?

136
00:15:40,647 --> 00:15:41,899
No.

137
00:15:42,274 --> 00:15:43,984
Not like this.

138
00:15:51,074 --> 00:15:52,826
Like this.

139
00:16:21,521 --> 00:16:24,107
I must be faithful to
the memory of my husband!

140
00:16:25,359 --> 00:16:28,654
I can't. I can't!

141
00:16:28,987 --> 00:16:32,658
It's not my fault... It's this place.

142
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:37,454
I feel strange tremors.

143
00:16:37,621 --> 00:16:38,997
It's not the cold...

144
00:16:39,206 --> 00:16:40,248
I'm not afraid...

145
00:16:40,707 --> 00:16:44,044
This place wants me to...
It's forcing me to...

146
00:16:46,421 --> 00:16:47,172
I don't want to!

147
00:16:49,549 --> 00:16:51,134
I don't want to!

148
00:16:53,929 --> 00:16:56,598
I can't! I can't!

149
00:19:41,930 --> 00:19:45,141
Don't be afraid, it's just ignis fatuus.

150
00:19:48,478 --> 00:19:49,604
Why here?

151
00:19:50,271 --> 00:19:52,732
Why on your poor husband's grave?

152
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:55,443
I've never kept anything from him...

153
00:19:55,652 --> 00:19:58,113
We trusted each other implicitly.

154
00:19:59,322 --> 00:20:01,116
He would have liked to know.

155
00:20:03,118 --> 00:20:05,954
Well, if that's the case...

156
00:20:15,255 --> 00:20:16,548
All these lights!

157
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:18,299
Let them watch.

158
00:20:18,633 --> 00:20:21,886
What's better than watching
two lovers making love, hey?

159
00:20:24,431 --> 00:20:27,267
Just to have a bit of privacy.

160
00:20:38,236 --> 00:20:41,698
Sorry, but the lady wants stars only.

161
00:22:12,580 --> 00:22:16,292
It's never been like
this before, with anybody.

162
00:22:16,542 --> 00:22:17,877
Only you.

163
00:22:18,294 --> 00:22:20,296
No one will ever make us part.

164
00:22:25,301 --> 00:22:27,262
Gnaghi! The gun!

165
00:22:29,264 --> 00:22:30,014
I can explain! Listen to me,

166
00:22:31,140 --> 00:22:32,934
you've always been so understanding!

167
00:22:33,434 --> 00:22:35,061
That's life!

168
00:22:56,874 --> 00:22:58,376
It's nothing my love,

169
00:22:58,584 --> 00:22:59,919
you're fine.

170
00:23:02,422 --> 00:23:03,548
Great,

171
00:23:03,756 --> 00:23:05,299
just when I don't need it anymore.

172
00:23:06,050 --> 00:23:09,178
Well don't just stand there!
Go call doctor Vercesi!

173
00:23:10,430 --> 00:23:12,849
Go on, get the doctor!

174
00:23:12,974 --> 00:23:15,476
Go on! Move!

175
00:23:16,185 --> 00:23:17,895
Nothing can separate us.

176
00:23:18,062 --> 00:23:20,314
I swear, nothing.

177
00:23:27,655 --> 00:23:30,783
Nothing will separate us, will it?

178
00:23:31,492 --> 00:23:33,786
Nothing, my love. Nothing.

179
00:23:37,248 --> 00:23:39,917
Not even death?

180
00:23:40,126 --> 00:23:41,961
Not even death.

181
00:24:19,165 --> 00:24:23,294
Dellamorte, are you
in there? Dellamorte!

182
00:24:36,766 --> 00:24:38,643
Jesus! You scared me to death!

183
00:24:38,851 --> 00:24:40,561
Were you looking for
me, Chief Straniero?

184
00:24:40,645 --> 00:24:43,189
Yes, Dr. Vercesi called.
What happened last night?

185
00:24:43,356 --> 00:24:45,525
Well you know. Why are
you asking me? She's dead.

186
00:24:45,733 --> 00:24:46,776
I know she's dead,

187
00:24:46,984 --> 00:24:48,486
but how did that happen?

188
00:24:49,737 --> 00:24:51,072
Her husband.

189
00:24:51,405 --> 00:24:54,075
Sure! He came back from
the dead, he raped her,

190
00:24:54,283 --> 00:24:55,785
then bit her to death.
Is that what he did?

191
00:24:55,952 --> 00:24:57,453
No, he didn't rape her.

192
00:24:57,662 --> 00:25:00,039
Oh, you always crack me up, you know!

193
00:25:00,248 --> 00:25:02,124
Dr. Vercesi, are you spying on us?

194
00:25:02,333 --> 00:25:04,001
No, I dropped this certificate.

195
00:25:04,085 --> 00:25:07,129
Her heart stopped from fear, it
wasn't the bite that killed her.

196
00:25:07,338 --> 00:25:11,217
She died while making...
well you know... doing it.

197
00:25:12,260 --> 00:25:14,011
You know what that means, my boy?

198
00:25:14,220 --> 00:25:16,555
I'll have to look somewhere else
for the creep who killed her!

199
00:25:16,806 --> 00:25:19,058
- You are no longer a suspect.
- Why not?

200
00:25:19,433 --> 00:25:21,852
Well, you know what I mean.

201
00:25:22,144 --> 00:25:23,896
Look, don't make me say it!

202
00:25:24,105 --> 00:25:27,024
Go on, you can say it. I
don't mind, I'm impotent!

203
00:25:27,191 --> 00:25:30,278
Don't use that word! A young
man like you, at your age...

204
00:25:30,486 --> 00:25:31,237
Did she have any relatives?

205
00:25:31,445 --> 00:25:33,698
No, no relatives, no friends.

206
00:25:36,158 --> 00:25:37,910
Well, I have to say that...

207
00:25:38,828 --> 00:25:40,037
Shit! This is definitely not my style!

208
00:25:43,833 --> 00:25:46,419
- Can I keep her here?
- If you pay for the funeral, of course

209
00:25:46,627 --> 00:25:48,212
you can do whatever
the hell you want with her.

210
00:25:48,546 --> 00:25:50,631
- Does that wrap it up, then?
- Yeah, except for a killer on the loose.

211
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:52,717
Care to join me for a cup of tea?

212
00:25:54,135 --> 00:25:56,637
The weather's changing at last!

213
00:26:16,907 --> 00:26:19,076
I can't forgive myself
for having lied to you:

214
00:26:20,119 --> 00:26:22,496
I don't have a degree in biology,

215
00:26:23,539 --> 00:26:25,624
I didn't even finish high school.

216
00:26:29,795 --> 00:26:32,840
I haven't read more than
two books in my whole life:

217
00:26:33,966 --> 00:26:35,843
one,

218
00:26:36,802 --> 00:26:38,596
never finished,

219
00:26:40,765 --> 00:26:42,933
and the other is the phone book.

220
00:27:03,204 --> 00:27:05,372
