221
00:27:05,915 --> 00:27:08,000
I don't want to see her again.

222
00:27:34,568 --> 00:27:35,820
No!

223
00:27:36,278 --> 00:27:37,988
Yes, my love!

224
00:27:39,406 --> 00:27:40,699
No, don't make me do it!

225
00:27:40,908 --> 00:27:43,118
But if you do it so well... so well!

226
00:27:44,995 --> 00:27:45,955
Not to you!

227
00:27:46,664 --> 00:27:48,749
It will be better with
me than with the others!

228
00:28:37,214 --> 00:28:38,173
Gna!

229
00:28:46,724 --> 00:28:47,891
You do it!

230
00:28:49,768 --> 00:28:53,272
Well go on! If you finish
fast I'll buy you an ice-cream.

231
00:28:53,397 --> 00:28:54,440
Gna!

232
00:29:04,366 --> 00:29:06,118
- Here comes the Unforgiven.
- Who?

233
00:29:06,327 --> 00:29:07,995
The Tombstone Mayor.

234
00:29:08,787 --> 00:29:12,374
The man whose dick's so
small he pees with tweezers.

235
00:29:15,711 --> 00:29:17,463
He could become a
woman. That'd solve it!

236
00:29:17,671 --> 00:29:20,591
They are sewing them
back on in the States now.

237
00:29:20,966 --> 00:29:23,093
Yeah, they can stitch it right on,
if you've got one to start with.

238
00:29:23,427 --> 00:29:25,095
Forget it, I started that rumour.

239
00:29:25,304 --> 00:29:27,181
The more they laugh, the
further away they seem.

240
00:29:27,514 --> 00:29:29,600
You can never be too different, Gnaghi.

241
00:29:31,226 --> 00:29:32,728
Maybe you can.

242
00:29:32,936 --> 00:29:34,605
Engineer!

243
00:29:35,814 --> 00:29:39,693
Engineer, engineer, come! Have a seat!

244
00:29:39,902 --> 00:29:42,946
Well well well, what a surprise!

245
00:29:43,197 --> 00:29:46,784
Yes! It's a miracle
seeing you here, engineer!

246
00:29:46,992 --> 00:29:49,536
It's a miracle seeing
you here, Mr. Mayor.

247
00:29:49,912 --> 00:29:54,083
So, how are things down at
our cemetery? How are things?

248
00:29:54,291 --> 00:29:55,876
Well how do you think things are?

249
00:29:56,085 --> 00:29:57,127
Population's shrinking.

250
00:29:57,336 --> 00:30:00,255
You're lucky, my dear engineer!

251
00:30:00,422 --> 00:30:03,675
You just can't imagine how
things are at the Town Hall.

252
00:30:03,759 --> 00:30:05,594
Now that the elections are upon us,

253
00:30:05,761 --> 00:30:08,222
it is chaos, right, inspector?

254
00:30:08,430 --> 00:30:11,517
Yeah, it's a thrill for all,
nobody wants to lose their job.

255
00:30:11,517 --> 00:30:13,393
I was hoping for a New Deal...

256
00:30:13,435 --> 00:30:15,687
Daddy, what's this?

257
00:30:15,896 --> 00:30:18,357
This is my assistant Gnaghi.

258
00:30:24,029 --> 00:30:25,280
He's sweet!

259
00:30:25,572 --> 00:30:27,199
Will you buy him, daddy?

260
00:30:28,659 --> 00:30:31,995
That's great, it even knows how to cry!

261
00:30:32,204 --> 00:30:33,831
Gnaghi, don't stay so close to her.

262
00:30:34,039 --> 00:30:35,791
Could you move over, darling?

263
00:30:35,958 --> 00:30:37,751
Would you tell your
daughter to move over please?

264
00:30:37,751 --> 00:30:38,836
Yes of course.

265
00:30:39,044 --> 00:30:40,671
Sometimes Gnaghi gets a little bit excited...

266
00:30:40,879 --> 00:30:43,006
Oh, I'm sure he's
charming. Now, where was I?

267
00:30:49,221 --> 00:30:51,598
What's he doing? Dancing?

268
00:30:51,807 --> 00:30:54,184
No, no, he's just about to...

269
00:30:58,021 --> 00:30:59,773
What the hell are you doing Valentina?

270
00:31:00,023 --> 00:31:02,025
He threw up on me, Claudio!

271
00:31:02,067 --> 00:31:03,443
Oh, a new fact!

272
00:31:03,819 --> 00:31:05,445
Would you like to go for a ride?

273
00:31:06,238 --> 00:31:08,115
I knew you'd understand!

274
00:31:09,116 --> 00:31:10,284
Take off!

275
00:31:15,414 --> 00:31:17,708
By the way, one of these days

276
00:31:17,916 --> 00:31:19,876
I have to talk to you
about the cemetery.

277
00:31:20,752 --> 00:31:25,382
The youth of today...
They're so... emotional.

278
00:31:33,724 --> 00:31:35,434
Come on, Gnaghi! Get in, for God's sake!

279
00:31:35,684 --> 00:31:37,811
Don't do this, just get in the car!

280
00:31:38,020 --> 00:31:40,939
It's not the end of the world,
It didn't even bother her!

281
00:31:41,148 --> 00:31:43,525
She understood it was just a
demonstration of your affection.

282
00:31:43,775 --> 00:31:47,446
Anyway, it's not the first time
you threw up over a woman, is it?

283
00:31:50,365 --> 00:31:52,618
Come on, Gnaghi, get in!

284
00:31:54,661 --> 00:31:57,289
Look, first love doesn't count.

285
00:31:57,497 --> 00:31:59,499
It's last love that counts!

286
00:32:07,674 --> 00:32:10,010
Nobody came today.

287
00:32:10,260 --> 00:32:11,970
I was a bit bored,

288
00:32:12,220 --> 00:32:15,557
not even the admiral...
he's just disappeared!

289
00:32:15,766 --> 00:32:18,477
Let's hope tomorrow, okay?

290
00:32:18,685 --> 00:32:21,021
Yeah, come again and stay a while.

291
00:32:21,229 --> 00:32:25,650
Oh, he was such a
distinguished man, the admiral!

292
00:32:25,859 --> 00:32:29,154
Always used to bring me, always,

293
00:32:29,363 --> 00:32:32,324
a touch of Sambuca.

294
00:33:05,357 --> 00:33:07,359
Oh, come on Gnaghi!

295
00:33:07,943 --> 00:33:09,402
You'll get over, you'll see!

296
00:33:12,614 --> 00:33:14,324
Time passes,

297
00:33:14,491 --> 00:33:16,034
nothing seems the same...

298
00:33:20,122 --> 00:33:21,998
It just gets worse.

299
00:33:22,749 --> 00:33:25,210
God, is it ever difficult
trying to make you feel better!

300
00:33:28,255 --> 00:33:31,383
What were you doing with the Mayor's
daughter anyway? She's only a child!

301
00:33:32,300 --> 00:33:33,343
Gna!

302
00:33:35,804 --> 00:33:39,099
Oh yeah, that's not true,
you are not a child, Gnaghi.

303
00:33:39,307 --> 00:33:42,561
You're a year older than I am. Anyway...

304
00:33:44,437 --> 00:33:45,272
One day,

305
00:33:45,480 --> 00:33:47,232
you'll settle down with some...

306
00:33:47,732 --> 00:33:49,818
poor creature like yourself.

307
00:33:53,613 --> 00:33:55,323
In the meanwhile, why do you care?

308
00:33:55,657 --> 00:33:58,410
They all end up here
sooner or later, Gnaghi.

309
00:33:59,202 --> 00:34:01,329
Often sooner than later.

310
00:34:03,081 --> 00:34:05,375
Faster, open it up!

311
00:34:07,586 --> 00:34:09,880
- If daddy could see us now!
- He'd kill me!

312
00:34:12,465 --> 00:34:13,633
Claudio!

313
00:34:13,842 --> 00:34:15,677
- Off we go!
- Go!

314
00:34:20,724 --> 00:34:22,475
Go! Go!

315
00:34:23,435 --> 00:34:24,686
Go!

316
00:34:34,070 --> 00:34:36,364
- Hang on!
- Eat our dust!

317
00:34:53,465 --> 00:34:55,008
Four motorcycles racing...

318
00:34:55,342 --> 00:34:56,676
The Mayor's daughter is on one of them.

319
00:34:56,968 --> 00:34:58,678
Her head was sliced right off.

320
00:34:58,845 --> 00:35:00,430
They had to sew it back on the body.

321
00:35:00,639 --> 00:35:03,683
The bikes crashed into
a bus loaded with scouts

322
00:35:03,892 --> 00:35:06,811
on their way back from
a church-sponsored rally.

323
00:35:06,978 --> 00:35:08,772
Slaughter of the innocents!

324
00:35:09,189 --> 00:35:10,774
And they were all so young.

325
00:35:11,524 --> 00:35:14,944
They felt their life was ahead of them,
but in fact they were already passing by.

326
00:35:15,320 --> 00:35:16,905
Well, you've got your hands full!

327
00:35:17,030 --> 00:35:18,782
Oh, more than you know!

328
00:35:19,282 --> 00:35:21,826
Gnaghi, we're going to
need a lot of bullets.

329
00:35:26,915 --> 00:35:30,043
# Never should have gone
out on the Boy Scout picnic,

330
00:35:30,377 --> 00:35:33,672
# never should have, never
should have gone just then.

331
00:35:34,005 --> 00:35:37,133
# Never should have gone
out on the Boy Scout picnic,

332
00:35:37,342 --> 00:35:41,137
# Never should have, now
I'll never go again! #

333
00:35:41,346 --> 00:35:43,014
Claudio! Take me with you!

334
00:35:43,223 --> 00:35:45,892
Don't leave me all alone, Claudio!

335
00:35:45,975 --> 00:35:47,852
Take me with you, my love!

336
00:35:48,603 --> 00:35:50,271
Nasty tart!

337
00:35:50,605 --> 00:35:53,066
My son wasn't with you!

338
00:35:53,233 --> 00:35:55,318
He was promised to the Mayor's daughter!

339
00:35:55,610 --> 00:35:57,987
- But he loved me!
- Liar!

340
00:35:58,238 --> 00:36:00,698
He was mine, he loved me!

341
00:36:01,074 --> 00:36:04,077
- Only me!
- Have you no respect for a mother's pain?

342
00:36:04,119 --> 00:36:06,538
We're born to die,

343
00:36:07,163 --> 00:36:09,165
born merely to die.

344
00:36:09,332 --> 00:36:11,000
Do you remember?

345
00:36:11,209 --> 00:36:12,627
Just yesterday,

346
00:36:12,794 --> 00:36:15,171
she was alive, happy.

347
00:36:15,380 --> 00:36:17,173
Do you remember?

348
00:36:17,465 --> 00:36:20,093
Dear Gnaghi even threw up on her,

349
00:36:20,385 --> 00:36:22,262
and she took it so well!

350
00:36:22,846 --> 00:36:25,557
And now, she's gone...

351
00:36:25,765 --> 00:36:28,518
and right on the eve of the elections!

352
00:36:28,726 --> 00:36:31,062
I better get the pickaxe and shovel.

353
00:36:31,771 --> 00:36:35,108
Pumpkin, how could you do this to me?

354
00:37:07,015 --> 00:37:09,017
Is it true as they say, that the
dead come back to life here at night?

355
00:37:09,184 --> 00:37:10,435
Tell me the truth!

356
00:37:10,685 --> 00:37:11,728
Hey! Who told you that?

357
00:37:12,020 --> 00:37:14,898
Is it true or not? Is it true or not?

358
00:37:15,190 --> 00:37:16,399
What if it is?

359
00:37:16,649 --> 00:37:19,110
I've got to see Claudio again!

360
00:37:19,319 --> 00:37:21,613
I have to know whether
he loved me or her!

361
00:37:21,863 --> 00:37:23,698
If I hear anything, I'll let you know.

362
00:37:24,741 --> 00:37:26,409
No, wait...

363
00:37:27,035 --> 00:37:29,245
Go away! I haven't got
time for the living!

364
00:38:08,952 --> 00:38:10,411
Gnaghi?

365
00:38:55,790 --> 00:38:56,833
Gnaghi!

366
00:38:57,458 --> 00:39:00,336
Gnaghi, they came back
sooner than we thought!

367
00:39:01,379 --> 00:39:03,089
Gnaghi wake up!

368
00:39:22,775 --> 00:39:24,068
Gnaghi, watch out!

369
00:40:28,174 --> 00:40:28,966
Gnaghi,

370
00:40:29,425 --> 00:40:32,637
I'm sorry, I didn't mean to.

371
00:40:42,647 --> 00:40:44,440
Well, that's it, time's up and

372
00:40:44,649 --> 00:40:47,902
I want you upstairs and
ready in five minutes! Okay?

373
00:42:01,058 --> 00:42:02,727
Oh no, what's she doing here?

374
00:42:16,198 --> 00:42:17,241
Visiting hours are over!

375
00:42:17,575 --> 00:42:19,660
No one is going to
take me away from him!

376
00:42:23,456 --> 00:42:24,790
Quick, get the fuck over here! Quick!

377
00:42:25,833 --> 00:42:27,793
No, Claudio!

378
00:43:08,792 --> 00:43:13,297
Claudio, take me with
you! Don't leave me!

379
00:43:13,881 --> 00:43:15,841
Stupid cow!

380
00:43:19,720 --> 00:43:21,055
Come on!

381
00:43:26,101 --> 00:43:28,270
Wait! Wait!

382
00:43:32,149 --> 00:43:34,860
Claudio please, take me with you!

383
00:43:35,110 --> 00:43:37,863
Tell me you only love me!

384
00:43:39,114 --> 00:43:40,616
Please...

385
00:43:57,091 --> 00:43:58,300
Claudio!

386
00:44:00,511 --> 00:44:03,055
You only love me, right?

387
00:44:28,664 --> 00:44:31,959
Damn! It always shoots to
the right when it's cold.

388
00:44:54,398 --> 00:44:55,566
Gnaghi!

389
00:45:34,980 --> 00:45:38,192
No, please don't! He's only eating me!

390
00:45:38,859 --> 00:45:39,693
Move aside.

391
00:45:40,152 --> 00:45:43,363
Mind your business! I shall
be eaten by whoever I please!

392
00:45:43,572 --> 00:45:46,200
This is my business. They pay me for it.

393
00:45:59,880 --> 00:46:01,256
The living dead

394
00:46:01,465 --> 00:46:04,510
and the dying living are all the same.

395
00:46:04,718 --> 00:46:07,137
Cut from the same cloth.

396
00:46:07,721 --> 00:46:10,933
But disposing of dead
people is a public service,

397
00:46:11,058 --> 00:46:13,435
whereas you're in all sorts of trouble

398
00:46:13,644 --> 00:46:16,688
if you kill someone
while they're still alive.

399
00:46:27,324 --> 00:46:28,450
Wait!

400
00:46:46,093 --> 00:46:48,178
This way they'll be together forever.

401
00:46:55,477 --> 00:46:57,145
I'm sentimental.

402
00:47:17,874 --> 00:47:19,584
Patience, Gnaghi.

403
00:47:19,793 --> 00:47:22,170
In love, it's the waiting
that's the best part.

404
00:47:23,755 --> 00:47:25,841
You have to learn how to wait.

405
00:48:44,836 --> 00:48:47,464
- What's your name again?
- Gna!

406
00:48:47,672 --> 00:48:49,382
Gnaghi.

407
00:48:54,554 --> 00:48:56,431
I'm Valentina.

408
00:48:57,349 --> 00:48:59,559
Haven't I seen you before?

409
00:49:01,186 --> 00:49:04,147
Oh yeah. Now I remember.

410
00:49:04,356 --> 00:49:06,650
You threw up on me. How sweet!

411
00:49:15,200 --> 00:49:17,285
But I like shy boys.

412
00:49:17,661 --> 00:49:20,330
And you never say no to a kiss.

413
00:49:20,455 --> 00:49:21,581
Take advantage.

414
00:49:22,332 --> 00:49:25,460
I'm certainly in no position
to refuse. Besides,

415
00:49:26,086 --> 00:49:27,420
I don't think I'd refuse anyway.

416
00:50:40,952 --> 00:50:42,412
False alarm!

417
00:50:43,663 --> 00:50:45,457
It was only a cat.

418
00:50:54,090 --> 00:50:56,926
No use you trying
to help me, little thing!

419
00:50:57,552 --> 00:50:59,846
If I can't do it, imagine you...

420
00:51:00,347 --> 00:51:02,974
Putting this skull together,

421
00:51:03,683 --> 00:51:06,478
is one of the most difficult
things in the world.

422
00:51:41,554 --> 00:51:43,848
You know, you really are
disgusting when you eat, Gnaghi.

